Title: No Good Deed
Description: Recover the supplies described in Huntsman Lee's requisition note and discover the fate of his porter, Riker.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Upon closer inspection there is a bloodstain on the note and the sound of wolves howling in the distance.
InProgressResponse: The note indicates someone named 'Riker' was out gathering food supplies when he was dragged away. \n\nWolf prints have tamped down the earth around the note.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oi, you're not Riker. Better looking than that old horse-faced lout, you are. \n\nBut look at what you bring! The people of the settlement need this food more than ever.

Title: Fine Furs For Fine Folk
Description: Acquire Midnight Hides from Midnight Den to replicate Huntsman Lee's fancy jacket for inquiring noble families.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: There's old money, the Publius, Sharma, and Ayad families, and then there's new money with the Sacco and Ou families. \n\nThey run this town with their coin, and have plenty to spare.
InProgressResponse: After doing your good deed for the day, it's only fitting you help yourself out, too. \n\nCollect those Midnight Hides and I'll make sure you see your fair share of coin.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, just feel how plush these pelts are! They're bloody perfect. \n\nThe noble families will be happy as a rabbit in a carrot field. Nice doing business with you, friend!

Title: A Circle of Stars
Description: Investigate towers Orion and Draco to acquire Ancient Devices, then return them with the notes to William Heron in the Everfall Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You spot a few hasty sketches in the margins, which appear to be diagrams of small Ancient devices.\n\nThis 'WH' might provide a decent reward for returning their notes and finding a few devices.
InProgressResponse: Most of the content in these notes is esoteric and hard to understand. \n\nOnly the directions to towers Orion and Draco are clear enough to follow.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Hmm? You don't look like an antiquarian. What business could you possibly have with--\n\nEgads, my notes! And you're carrying some of those peculiar Ancient devices. Does this mean you visited the towers yourself?

Title: Stellar Research
Description: Investigate towers Perseus and Lupus, then return to William Heron to tell him what you found.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Perish the thought! You'll handle anything in the field. We will both be credited on any works I write. \n\nAnd of course, you will be compensated with coin and any… hmm… items that are irrelevant to my studies.
InProgressResponse: From what I can glean, the Ancients place neither sun nor earth at the center of creation. \n\nTo them, the heavens are an endless void with no center. It's quite impossible to picture.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You look a bit worse for wear. I do apologize for sending you in blind. \n\nI had no luck finding any records of either Perseus or Lupus, aside from some useless myths about celestial wolves.

Title: Beacons in the Dark
Description: Investigate towers Norma, Leo, and Hercules and see if there is a way to activate them.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Not particularly. I confess that at this point, you have more practical experience with the towers than I do. \n\nI may need to promote you to co-author on my thesis at this rate.
InProgressResponse: I suspect that the skeletal guardians are unintelligent. Less like men, more like clockwork mindlessly ticking on. \n\nOf course, that doesn't make them any less ferocious. Someday, you'll have to show me how to dispatch them.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Your very presence caused the towers to glow? \n\nThere's no rhyme or reason to these damnable buildings! First the defenders attack you, but then the towers respond to you? I struggle to make sense of it.

Title: Azoth Awakening
Description: Collect Azoth Dust from Ancient Guardians at towers Canus, Ursa, and Monoceros.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: …\n\n… A predictable answer. The next time you destroy them, could you bring back samples from their remains?
InProgressResponse: Surely you aren't put off by a few samples from long-dead skeletons? \n\nHmm. Perhaps I could've phrased that better, now that I think about it…
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: This azoth is only slightly contaminated with human bone dust. It will suffice. \n\nThese defenders must have been made for a special purpose, and the azoth samples should illuminate that purpose.

Title: Constellation Convergence
Description: Retrieve the Armillary Sphere from the Shattered Obelisk, along with Ancient Runekeys held by its defenders. Return them to William Heron, who hopes to unlock the Armillary Sphere.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Accurate, if simple. The Ancients employed them as well, though theirs were far more complex. \n\nBetween the astronomical names of each tower and my own prior research, I believe an armillary sphere is the key to reactivating the tower system.
InProgressResponse: I can only imagine what Aeternum looked like during the reign of the Ancients. I feel we would have gotten along swimmingly, don't you? \n\nThough I wish they'd deigned to leave better instructions for their creations…
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: At last, the armillary sphere! I'll insert the keys, and… hmm. That's unexpected. \n\nThe good news is that I now know the purpose of the obelisks. They drew power from the heavens to protect the land against Corruption.

Title: Foreman's Ledger (Expedition)
Description: Collect the Foreman's Ledger in Amrine Excavation. Report back to William Heron in the Everfall Settlement when your task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Simon led the expedition into the Amrine Excavation of Windsward many years ago, and never returned.\n\nI still say the real genius behind Simon was his Foreman, who mapped every Ancient Ruin in all Aeternum.
InProgressResponse: The Amrine Excavation is a dangerous digsite, so you will likely need friends to safely explore it. \n\nDo not go in underprepared, unless you enjoy the experience of dying.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Is that it? His ledger? Fantastic! With this, I can learn a great deal!\n\nSome of the notes he made here… fascinating. Who knew?

Title: Starstone of Shattering (Expedition)
Description: Collect the Starstone Diadem from Greundgul the Regent inside the Shattered Obelisk. Report back to William Heron in the Everfall Settlement when your task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes, the Foreman's notes suggest the existence of a side entrance that could actually allow a small group to get inside.\n\nCan you imagine the secrets hidden in there? You must go there for me! You must!
InProgressResponse: Oh, the possibilities! We could be unearthing an artifact that helps us fight the Corrupted, or at the very least gives us insight into the Ancients. \n\nPlease, make haste to the Shattered Obelisk so you might obtain this Diadem of power.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: This is truly a momentous find. This Starstone Diadem seems to have denoted an Ancient Guardian of incredibly high ranking, a ruler of some sort! \n\nA regent, perhaps? Oh, I simply must get to studying it further.

Title: Dishonorable Daughter
Description: Venture into Arcturus to recover an item of equal value to the one Tamra Ayad destroyed in her home estate, and return the item to Tamra Ayad.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Everyone! After what I've done. In my clumsiness, I knocked over and shattered grandmother's favorite vase. \n\nIt was irreplaceable, a family heirloom from the old world. Now I'm all alone…
InProgressResponse: Look for anything valuable, large, pristine, or beautiful. Going back to my family depends upon it. \n\nS-Sorry. No pressure…
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Look at that, what a beauty! This will definitely get me back in grandmother's good graces! You've saved my life, friend. \n\nBut on second thought… I should make certain this is what I think it is.

Title: Curious Child
Description: Bring the Ancient Scrolls to Tamra Ayad to assess their value.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You pick up the writings and decide to bring them to Tamra Ayad, the woman who asked you to find a vase in Arcturus.
InProgressResponse: The scrolls sit waiting to be taken to someone who understands their value.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: What's this? More Ancient relics? Oh! Writings! \n\nGrandmother won't appreciate these. They hardly draw the eye. But I'll find a better use for them than sitting in our manor, collecting dust.

Title: An Heir Transformed
Description: Venture into the Varangian camp to recover the stolen Ancient relics for Tamra Ayad.
PlayerPrompt: "You aren't bringing the vase back home?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Not just the vase. I feel… this place better suits me. Finally, I can explore my own interests! \n\nBut that brings me to my purpose here. We've heard disturbing rumors about looters in the vicinity.
InProgressResponse: I doubt the knights will part with their finds willingly. \n\nThose relics would be much better off in the hands of proper scholars than a band of thugs.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oh my! You recovered so many! They must have been hoarding these like squirrels. \n\nAh, look at the damage they suffered. Such a shame, but they could still offer insights. I only wish…

Title: Canary in the Corrupted Mine
Description: Scout the land of Canary Mine to investigate the Corrupted threat.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The kind that can take what you value most, so you best keep your wits about you. \n\nThen again, you seem to be more aware of the danger that menaces us.
InProgressResponse: I have been developing this poison ever since… \n\nWell, I shall not burden you with a sob story when we've only just become acquainted.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: The earth of Canary Mine will yield no more for the Corrupted. Good. \n\nLet them starve. Let them feel the sting of privation.

Title: Salting the Earth
Description: Poison the earth of Ebonrock Cavern and Ebonrock Quarry while taking down as many Corrupted as you can for Tekla Petrowski.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Then they are fools. Corruption is real, it is here, and it will take so much more from us than we could ever expect.\n\nI've stared into the face of that evil. I know what must be done.
InProgressResponse: The quarry and cavern used to be some of the most prosperous mines in Everfall.\n\nEverything changed when the Corrupted attacked.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: It is done. All my poison has been used, and it will take months to create a new batch.\n\nI thought… I thought it would quell the rage, but I don't feel any different.

Title: Tekla's Tragedy
Description: Venture to the Everfall Settlement to discuss the Corrupted incursion with Huntsman Odnell Lee.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Odnell Lee is a friend.\n\nHe may play every political side in Everfall, but he has proven trustworthy when it counts. Go speak to him.
InProgressResponse: We used to be closer, Lee and I. That was when… Nevermind.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Wait… you're saying that Tekla did what to the mines?!\n\nOh, my… I have a terrible feeling this is about Audrey.

Title: Avenging Audrey
Description: Shame the Corrupted forces occupying Kelleher's Farmstead by taking out the Lieutenants and speak to Tekla Petrowski.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: So, Lee told you about Audrey… Yes, this is for her. She was killed in her own home and never came back. \n\nI don't know why this happened, only that it forever changed the trajectory of my life.
InProgressResponse: Audrey was too good for this island. Too good for this world.\n\nI'm no warrior, myself. But you, you can reap enough vengeance for us both.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: So the lieutenants have been defeated. Good. \n\nThey deserve much worse, but this will suffice for now.

Title: Bittersweet Memory
Description: Return the Lost Locket to Tekla Petrowski.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You pocket the locket with the intent of showing it to Tekla Petrowski.
InProgressResponse: The locket is dusty and lonely. \n\nPerhaps it will find a new home with Tekla Petrowski.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: What are you holding? Could it be…?\n\nI thought the locket was lost forever. Thank you for finding it. Oh, my Audrey...

Title: The Lovers' Flowers
Description: Touched by your return of the locket, Tekla Petrowski wishes for you to gather a bouquet of Meadowlake Flowers at Meadowlake Fishery to remember Audrey.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: No. It is too painful. But if you find yourself heading in the direction of Meadowlake Fishery perhaps you could gather a bouquet for her? \n\nNo matter where she is, what became of her… I think Audrey would like that.
InProgressResponse: I have already asked so much of you, but here I am, asking for the tiniest bit of comfort. \n\nYou're a kind soul. Audrey would have liked you, I think…
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Your willingness to help a stranger has taught me much. \n\nIt's not just about hating the Corrupted, it's about loving the living while you can.

Title: Lee's Condolences
Description: Relay what has happened with Tekla Petrowski to Odnell Lee in the Everfall Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Not today. But perhaps tomorrow, or the day after that. \n\nYou needn't worry about me. You've done enough, and I promise not to forget your kindness.
InProgressResponse: Lee is a kind man, and he's fussed over me ever since I lost Audrey to the Corrupted. \n\nGo and ease his mind, he deserves that much.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You're back! You must've done something incredible to soothe the tempest in Tekla's heart. \n\nLosing Audrey nearly destroyed her, and I felt so damn helpless watching it happen. Thank you. Because of you, I didn't lose another friend.

Title: The Magnum Opus
Description: Longing to rise above his station as a butler, Atticus Delphi wishes to share his musical talents with the world. With so many instruments to choose from, he is struck with a moment of indecision.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Alas, I should have chosen a more private locale for this. \n\nCould you kindly forget what you saw and heard? My mistress would be quite irate, if she learned I've been sneaking away to work on such a frivolous pursuit.
InProgressResponse: A guitar may very well be suitable, but I will know the true voice of my work when I hear it. \n\nAs for the instruments… hmm, I suggest you start with Magistrate Clark. He is a known lover of music.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ahhh… there it is. The flute produces the most whimsical sound. I can elicit soul-stirring melodies from such an instrument. \n\nYes, this will do nicely. You hold onto it, for now. We will return it later, along with the rest.

Title: Reputation is Everything
Description: What good is a composition if it goes unheard? Play the Magnum Opus throughout the town in a grand debut as a composer!
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I cannot be the one to deliver my work unto the world. To gain a reputation for being a GREAT composer, we must create the impression that my music has spread far and wide. \n\nIn this business, as in many others, reputation is everything.
InProgressResponse: If you want to embellish a little, perhaps you could also mention how prolific my work is. \n\nI have more compositions, of course, but none have seen the light of day as of yet.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: How did it go? Did they like it? Did their eyes shine? Perhaps shed a tear? \n\nI wish I could have seen their reactions for myself, but there are more important things. Did it make an impact? Is there now a reputation I must uphold?

Title: It's Who You Know
Description: With his reputation growing with each passing day, now is the time to seek a patron. One does not simply approach the patriarch of a great house on a whim, however…
PlayerPrompt: "That seems harsh. What are you going to do?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Find a patron without her, obviously. She does not own me. \n\nI did some sleuthing and discovered that the Ou family recently lost a musician in their employ. If we tread carefully, I can present myself to the patriarch.
InProgressResponse: There are other avenues, but they are less socially acceptable. \n\nI must maintain an appearance of uncompromised integrity in everything that I do, even the smallest of social details.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I detect triumph in your demeanor. I do not know what you had to do to secure this opportunity for me, but I suspect victory is close at hand. \n\nAnd now, we wait.

Title: Everyone has a Price
Description: The great family Sacco will not be humiliated so easily. With Atticus bound to his contractual duties, his patron may be the only one who can set him free to practice his craft.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Thank you… my heart is all aflutter. Perhaps you could act as my associate and accompany me? \n\nI know this may be beneath you, but think of how it will reflect on the reputation we worked so hard to build!
InProgressResponse: I am so nervous I could sweat through my socks. How humiliating would that be? \n\nGet it together, Atticus. You are a consummate professional.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You return. \n\nWell? Shall I deliver the good news to Atticus?

Title: Ever Been Mauled?
Description: Felix Livius challenges you to "wrestle" a bear for the raw thrill of it all.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Almost every day! It's a great way to wake yourself up, squaring up with a fuzzy behemoth of nature. \n\nDoesn't even hurt after awhile. All I can feel when I bring a beast down is the sting of victory.
InProgressResponse: Still hanging around here? \n\nYou ought to be wrestling a bear, and we both know it. Scared?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Haha! You've done it! Good for you, showing some true brawn. \n\nNext time? Try fighting it with no weapons at all. Bare fists versus bear fists. You'll never know a sweeter victory.

Title: Bragging Rights
Description: Talk to Huntsman Lee in the Everfall Settlement about your bear experience.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I'm just an enthusiast. Odnell, though? Cares too much about appearances. But Aeternum's full of all sorts. \n\nGo tell him you defeated a bear, and he'll make sure everyone in Oxboro knows it.
InProgressResponse: Lost, are we? Huntsman Lee is in Oxboro, so he shouldn't be too hard to find. \n\nGo report your victory!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You did what, with a WHAT?! A bear! \n\nNow, that takes serious guts. Did you wind up spilling yours in the fight?

Title: Hope in a Bottle
Description: The Lost Pirates of the Riverworn Grotto have stolen Jacob Evans' last shipment of mead, driving him to the brink of despair.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I should. I would, if not for dear Polly. Her business depends on the mead that I bring, but I'm just a porter. \n\nI can't stop those wretched pirates from taking everything and stabbing me through. I've lost count...
InProgressResponse: Polly deserves better than me. Someone strong, brave, and true of heart. \n\nBut folks like that only exist in children's tales.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: My… mead? I can't believe my eyes. \n\nI'm sorry, I'm so sorry. I really did think you were having a laugh at me earlier. But you meant every word you said.

Title: No Time for Wine
Description: With his mead returned, Jacob Evans turns his attention to his next source of woe: a shipment of missing wine.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Look at me, friend. A lonely man with his wits barely about him, marching from one town to the next on his own two legs. \n\nI'm an easy target no matter how careful I am, or which road I take.
InProgressResponse: Please, if you can't find the wine, just… leave me to my fate. \n\nThe mead's not enough to save Polly's bar. Nothing I do is ever enough.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: That's almost every missing bottle. I don't know what to say. \n\nI haven't much to repay you, not after what you've done for me.

Title: Master and Commandaria
Description: Jacob Evans has remembered the name of one of his tormentors. Help him get some revenge on Admiral Arias.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: This time, it's not about my goods. Someone ought to teach him a lesson. \n\nHe's a coward, preying on decent folk who can't fight back. But he won't expect anybody to march up and thrash him.
InProgressResponse: What do the Lost want with my wares? Can they even taste the sweetness of mead? \n\nSmell the rich aroma of a good vintage? What a waste.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Let me see the label on that old bottle. It's covered in dust, but this writing… could it be? \n\nIt is! The wine of kings, the king of wines, the Commandaria of Cyprus! The knights Templar once sold this wine.

Title: Raising the Bar
Description: Jacob is entrusting you with delivering the priceless bottle of Commandaria to Polly's bar, in the hopes that it will save her business.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Certain. I would love to deliver it myself, but I'm content knowing Polly's saved. \n\nBe careful. Don't wave that bottle around, or anyone who knows its value will be after your blood.
InProgressResponse: Polly's livelihood depends on that bottle. Wrap it up, and make sure the label's covered. \n\nYou may think I'm exaggerating, but trust me. That's the most valuable vintage anywhere on the island.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Let's see what we have here. Commandaria? From the island of Cyprus? \n\nThis is enough to save my bar, and then some! I could even buy a nice little cottage with what's left over.

Title: Cure For What Ails You
Description: The wares that Anwir is hawking seem a little suspect. Nevertheless, he's happy to pay for help "improving" them.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Shh! Not so loud! Are you trying to bring the guards down on my head? \n\nListen, a man has to make a living . And it's all harmless, I promise. I wouldn't sell anything that would hurt a fly.
InProgressResponse: I need a better name for the product. Anwir's Elixir just doesn't sound impressive enough. \n\n Anwir's Miracle Elixir? Or better yet, Anwir's Ancient Miracle Elixir!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: A fine piece of liver and a perfect ram's horn. You sure you haven't done this before? \n\nNow, we shave off a bit of the horn, grind up some liver, and there it is. A healthy addition to Anwir's Ancient Miracle Elixir.

Title: The Secret Ingredient
Description: Anwir Hughes is back, with another scheme to "improve" his Ancient Miracle Elixir.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You wound me! Yes, the latest version of the elixir was pungent, but I know how to solve that little problem. \n\nHydrangeas. They were my grandfather's favorite blossom. They'll do the trick, I just know it.
InProgressResponse: Unfortunately, we'll need many flowers for just one bottle of elixir. \n\nIt pains me to pick the hillside bare, but that is the price we pay for the best possible product!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Such lovely hydrangeas. You, my friend, have a knack for spotting good potion ingredients. \n\nLook, they even improve the elixir's color, not just the scent. I think we have gold in a bottle here.

Title: Potions for the People
Description: Nothing can go wrong with distributing Anwir's Ancient Miracle Elixir to the people of Everfall, right?
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Who better than you? You've got that heroic look, and you radiate a certain aura of… trustworthiness. \n\nIt's a gift that not all of us have. Especially not me.
InProgressResponse: If you get cold feet, just remember: there's coin in it for you too. \n\nIn all seriousness, I would never sell anything I won't drink myself. I swear it on my grandfather's memory.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: As of today, I've sold at least a dozen orders of Anwir's Ancient Miracle Elixir. They're going faster than I can make them! \n\nAnd of course, I would never forget to pay my best friend in this endeavor.

Title: Bottle It Up
Description: Try to piece together the strange alchemical recipe, then bring it to a Syndicate alchemist for further study.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You carefully copy down the legible text from the paper fragment, but it's meaningless on its own. \n\nYou need more information to make sense of it.
InProgressResponse: By itself, this scrap of paper is useless to you. \n\nThe glass bottles scattered around it may contain some clues.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Hm? What's that you've got?  "Superiora de inferioribus, inferiora de superioribus." \n\nDo you have any idea what you've found? This recipe may reveal the very nature of the cosmos to us!

Title: Miner's Keepers
Description: One ill-fated miner's find is another better-fated miner's treasure.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The dusty, smeared, badly crumpled parchment appears to be a hand-drawn charcoal map of north-western Everfall.\n\nA section of rocky valley is circled several times, indicating a significant find.
InProgressResponse: The dusty, smeared, badly crumpled parchment appears to be a hand-drawn charcoal map of north-western Everfall.\n\nA section of rocky valley is circled several times, indicating a significant find.

Title: The Yearly Convergence
Description: Welcome to the Winter Convergence! Check out the Holiday Huts in the Winter Villages to see what items can be crafted there.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: We must chase away cold. First, by warming hearts.\n\n{playerName}, are you prepared to do whatever it takes to save Aeternum?
InProgressResponse: Village here has huts. Huts have shiny coins. Trade coins for goods. Many, many goods! They will help your journey.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: This year has much waiting for you if you bring warmth back to Aeternum.\n\nWinter, cold, and eternal darkness can be held back by you.

Title: Lost Presents
Description: Find and return a Lost Present of the many around Aeternum to the Winter Wanderer in the Winter Village.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Collect presents taken by other Yeti and their ice creatures.\n\nDevious minds scatter presents all over the island.
InProgressResponse: Have you found wayward presents?\n\nSome suspend in air, locked into place by winter magics.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: This gift… makes me remember… \n\nI was lost on a mountain, in a terrible winter storm. A bright star led me into a cave. When I came out the other side, I was here in Aeternum.

Title: The Power of Gleamite
Description: Mine a fallen Gleamite Crystal and return it to the Winter Wanderer in the Winter Village.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Tinkling, ringing with the sound of laughter are these crystals.\n\nTheir heat harms the Winter Warrior as they fall from the sky to light the land.
InProgressResponse: I have marked on your map where a Gleamite Crystal can be found.\n\nAt night they fall, twinkling like stars crashing down to earth.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Thank you, {playerName}. You have done much, but I am afraid I must ask for more help still.\n\nThe Winter Warrior must fall.

Title: Forever Winter
Description: Locate the Winter Warrior's spread of the Forever Winter <img src="lyshineui/images/map/icon/pois/winter_warrior" xPadding="0" scale="2.5" yOffset="5.2"></img>and collect his Hailspikes as proof of victory against the chiling threat.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Perhaps. Do not fret.\n\nBeast or man, The Winter Warrior must be taken down. Are you willing to accept the challenge?
InProgressResponse: The Winter Warrior is formidable foe. Take friends, allies, and all you can to defeat him.\n\nCome together with people of Aeternum to push back Forever Winter.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: He is defeated! Oh joy, oh beautiful day!\n\nA peaceful Convergence is possible now. Should he appear again, you know what to do.

Title: Truffle Fever
Description: Collect any Truffles you can find in the forest and bring them to Hapless Howe in the settlement. Look for any Herbs or Berries you can gather as well.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: How should I know? Do I look like some kind of "boar-mind-reader"? Not me. I'm just a simple Traveling Herbalist.\n\nTell you this much, however, the beasts have ruined me for the season.
InProgressResponse: Sad days are these when a traveling Herbalist has to rely on the goodwill of a stranger to make ends meet.\n\nBut if you'll bring me some truffles in the settlement, I'll have a little something for you.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Here's my new friend, right here! All the truffles I lost and then some! I hope it wasn't too hard!\n\nKeep that sickle for your troubles, and if you make a habit of Harvesting herbs and such, we'll cross paths again, no doubt.

Title: The Winter Convergence
Description: Welcome to the Winter Convergence! Check out the Holiday Huts in the Winter Village to see what items can be crafted there.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Winter, cold, darkness… mind filled with dark mists… words hard… \n\nWarmer here, by tree. Warmer with people. Hol-i-day Hut will help.
InProgressResponse: Village here has huts. Huts have shiny coins. Trade coins for goods. Many, many goods! They will help you.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Winter coins allow many trades. Much to do in village. \n\nWords are returning. Listen, listen close…

Title: Tree of Light
Description: Collect your first daily rewards from the Tree of Light in any settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Winter is cold, bitter, lonely. But also time for warmth, comfort, joy. Two sides of winter, {playerName}. They must come together. \n\nHere in village we are warm with trees and huts and gifts. Out in wilderness, yetis shape ice into caves.
InProgressResponse: We are safe here in Winter Village.\n\nLook in sack of gifts. Admire Trees of Light. These will warm the land.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Your smile… yes, it is good… it feels familiar. \n\nThis is what I must do. Bring smiles to faces. This will warm the land.

Title: All Together Now
Description: View the Town Projects Board to see the progress of upgrading the Tree of Light.
PlayerPrompt: "You seem to be remembering more as we go on."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes, {playerName}. I remember the sound of bells, of children laughing… But I also remember the sound of frigid winds, a darkness that must be pushed back. Helping Tree of Light might stave off darkness.
InProgressResponse: Forever Winter is great threat to island. All green turns to white, all water turns to ice. Tree of Light keeps light on against darkness. Working with settlement is only way to make Tree brighter, make community stronger.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I… I'm recalling more. Speaking is getting easier. Maybe if I keep talking to you, friend, I will get more memories back.

Title: Gleamite Crystals
Description: Mine a fallen Gleamite crystal and return it to the Winter Wanderer in the Winter Village.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: They fall to Aeternum at night. Look to the night sky, friend {playerName}. \n\nUse your hands to break the crystals free. Collect the fragments.
InProgressResponse: Bring me Gleamite crystals. Search high and low for the fallen chunks at night or go to the place I mark on map. \n\nTheir light will warm the land.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: The lights of these star crystals conjures a name… Mirgos. Was that my name? \n\nYes, it must have been! It feels good to say it. What a great gift to have a name once more. Thank you!

Title: Joy Recaptured
Description: Find and return a Lost Present of the many around Aeternum to the Winter Wanderer in the Winter Village.
PlayerPrompt: "I'm glad your words and memory are coming back."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes, {playerName}. I remember the sound of bells, children laughing… \n\nBut I also remember the sound of howling wind, an ever-growing darkness. Tending the Tree of Light will push back the darkness.
InProgressResponse: Forever Winter threatens the land. But the Tree of Light can protect against the darkness. \n\nWork with human villages and find gifts. You must make the Tree of Light shine bright and warm the land.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: This gift… makes me remember… \n\nI was lost on a mountain, in a terrible winter storm. A bright star led me into a cave. When I came out the other side, I was here in Aeternum.

Title: Yetis Abound
Description: Defeat the Level 25 feral yetis spreading icy magic across the island. Defeat Rames in Everfall, Hari in Monarch's Bluffs, and Sunit in First Light.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Good! To protect all life on  Aeternum from Forever Winter, the yetis must be defeated. \n\nTravelers have given me the locations of three of the monsters.
InProgressResponse: The yetis in these ice caves will be formidable. Take great caution when confronting them. \n\nThese monsters are servants of the will of the Forever Winter.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Well done, celebrant and friend! By weakening the yetis, we have hampered their ability to cover more of Aeternum in ice.\n\nThe power of the Winter Wanderer Mirgos grows as warmth spreads throughout the land.

Title: Wanderer Reborn
Description: Harvest Gleamite Chunks, recover Lost Presents, collect daily rewards from the Tree of Light and Gift Sack, and complete Festive Town Projects to reach rank three of reputation with the Winter Wanderer and speak to the Winter Wanderer in the Winter Village.
PlayerPrompt: "Why did this voice send you to Aeternum?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I do not know. But I must find out. I believe the more we attend to our tasks, the more I shall remember. \n\nWill you continue to collect Gleamite crystals and Lost Presents? Will you continue to spread joy and cheer to the settlements through town projects and daily collections?
InProgressResponse: You must continue to spread warmth and joy across the island. Do enough of this and I will remember more. Harvest Gleamite Chunks, recover Lost Presents, collect daily rewards from the Tree of Light and Gift Sack, and complete Festive Town Projects. \n\nTogether, we may yet be able to stave off the Forever Winter!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Look at all you have done. You have embodied the spirit of Winter Convergence! \n\nMy memories return. I now remember the dreadful figure who brings the endless cold… The Winter Warrior.

Title: Winter Warrior
Description: Collect Runestone Fragments from Isvari in Edengrove and Sesa in Ebonscale Reach to locate the cave of the Winter Warrior and defeat the mastermind within.
PlayerPrompt: "I am as strong as I can be."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Very well. Then we must track down the Winter Warrior. He is savage and cunning, and he commands the other yetis.\n\nThis is the enemy the Voice in the wind sent me to defeat. The Spirit of Winter Convergence brought us together on Aeternum to determine the fate of all.
InProgressResponse: Isvari in Edengrove and Sesa in Ebonscale Reach hold runestones that will lead you to the Winter Warrior. Offer the stones at the Warrior's cave to summon him. \n\nThe fate of Aeternum's winter is in your hands now, friend of Mirgos.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I felt the Winter Warrior's defeat the moment you struck him down! Aeternum is now safe!\n\nThere is still more cheer to be shared, though. Next year I shall return and see your progress. For now, continue doing activities in the Winter Village and settlements to spread the Spirit of Convergence!

Title: Enter The Arena
Description: Maximus Marcellus invites you to participate in a team versus team extravaganza. Enter by queueing from the Map.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: What is the Arena? Why, it is in the grand tradition of my motherland of Rome, it is a battle spectacular of two teams going head-to-head in combat!\n\nIt requires skill, coordination, and an unshakable mettle to participate.
InProgressResponse: To enter the Arena you can open your Map and use Modes to sign up for the Arena Grounds.\n\nWhat are you waiting for? Get out there and pummel!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: What a show! I was on the edge of my seat the entire time! You, my friend, are a sure addition to the Arena roster.\n\nReturn to fight any time, you are always welcome here my fearsome champion!
